This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with scene recognition research and image feature counts. It also involves the use of a generative model to capture variation in feature counts, which is a common approach in computer vision. The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which makes it likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper may also be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories as it deals with the representation and analysis of visual data.
